value.value: the presence of one or more holes in part of the base of the cranium between the basioccipital and the presphenoid, which usually ossifies separately in the embryo or in the young, and becomes a part of the sphenoid in the adult; in many animals it persists as a separate bone between the basioccipital bone and the presphenoidal bone

label.value: absent strial basal cell tight junctions

value.value: absence of tight junctions from the basal cell layer of stria vascularis, resulting in destruction of the paracellular barrier between basal cells; loss of basal cell tight junctions renders the intrastrial space open to perilymph and abolishes its electrical isolation

label.value: degeneration of organ of Corti supporting cells

value.value: degeneration or loss of the highly differentiated epithelial cells with distinctive morphological features that surround all hair cells in the organ of Corti
reduced height of the sensory cells of the organ of Corti which are in synaptic contact with sensory as well as efferent fibers of the auditory nerve
absence of the quadrilateral bone that forms the prominence of the cheek
reduced size of the quadrilateral bone that forms the prominence of the cheek

any structural anomaly of the bony arch in vertebrates that extends along the side or front of the skull beneath the eye socket and is formed by the temporal process of the zygomatic bone and the zygomatic process of the temporal bone
reduced size of either of two rectangular bone plates forming the bridge of the nose
reduced length of either of two rectangular bone plates forming the bridge of the nose
increased width of either of two rectangular bone plates forming the bridge of the nose
absence of either of two rectangular bone plates forming the bridge of the nose
increased size of either of two rectangular bone plates forming the bridge of the nose

underdevelopment or reduced size, usually due to a reduced number of cells, in either of either of two irregularly L-shaped bones located posterior to the maxilla that in part forms the back of the hard palate, part of the nasal cavity and part of the floor of the orbits
absence of either of two irregularly L-shaped bones located posterior to the maxilla that in part forms the back of the hard palate, part of the nasal cavity and part of the floor of the orbits
underdevelopment or reduced size, usually due to a reduced number of cells, in the small curved bones that extends horizontally along the lateral wall of the nasal passage

greater than the expected number of a usually benign tumor found in the testis that is the result of an anomaly of germ cell development, occurring in a specific population in a given time period; teratomas typically contains a diversity of tissues often representing all organ systems such as hair, teeth, bone, thyroid, or nerve tissue
any structural anomaly of the oval opening on the medial wall of the tympanic cavity leading into the vestibule, close to the foot of the stapes

any structural anomaly of the conjunctival layer of epithelial cells covering inner surface of the eyelid and the front of the eyeball except over the cornea

label.value: altered response of heart to induced stress

label.value: increased response of heart to induced stress

label.value: decreased response of heart to induced stress

label.value: type I spiral ligament fibrocyte degeneration

label.value: type II spiral ligament fibrocyte degeneration

value.value: degeneration or loss of type II spiral ligament fibrocytes found in the suprastrial zone and the central area of the spiral ligament beneath the spiral prominence

label.value: type III spiral ligament fibrocyte degeneration

value.value: degeneration or loss of type III spiral ligament fibrocytes which form a cell layer attached to the otic capsule

label.value: type IV spiral ligament fibrocyte degeneration

value.value: degeneration or loss of type IV spiral ligament fibrocytes found in the triangular space inferior to the basilar crest

label.value: abnormal orientation of outer hair cell stereociliary bundles

value.value: misorientation or rotation of outer hair cell (OHC) stereociliary bundles, resulting in defective planar cell polarity of the inner ear sensory epithelium

label.value: abnormal orientation of inner hair cell stereociliary bundles

value.value: misorientation or rotation of inner hair cell (IHC) stereociliary bundles, resulting in defective planar cell polarity of the inner ear sensory epithelium
the luminal space of the cochlea is increased in volume or area, usually with an increase in contained fluid

aberrant secretion across synapses of the major excitatory neurotransmitter of the central nervous system (CNS), which acts through both ligand gated ion channels (ionotropic receptors) and G protein-coupled (metabotropic) receptors

reduced secretion across synapses of the major excitatory neurotransmitter of the central nervous system (CNS), which acts through both ligand gated ion channels (ionotropic receptors) and G protein-coupled (metabotropic) receptors

label.value: abnormal organ of Corti supporting cell number

label.value: decreased organ of Corti supporting cell number

label.value: increased organ of Corti supporting cell number

value.value: increased number of the highly differentiated epithelial cells with distinctive morphological features which surround the hair cells in the organ of Corti

label.value: increased incidence of tumors by chemical induction

value.value: higher than normal frequency of tumor incidence induced by one or more chemical carcinogens or mutagens

label.value: increased incidence of tumors by ionizing radiation induction

value.value: higher than normal frequency of tumor incidence induced by radiation in which the individual particle or photon carries sufficient energy to completely remove an electron from its orbit; common types of this radiation include gamma-rays and X-rays

label.value: increased incidence of tumors by UV-induction

value.value: higher than normal frequency of tumor incidence induced by exposure to ultraviolet light

label.value: decreased incidence of tumors by chemical induction

label.value: decreased incidence of tumors by ionizing radiation induction
